---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="System Integration | Intelio - Connect Your Systems" description="Connect CRMs, accounting, operations, and data systems. One connected stack instead of disconnected tools.">
<main class="bg-white">
  <!-- HERO SECTION: Video Background -->
  <section class="relative h-[600px] md:h-[450px] sm:h-[300px] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden bg-black">
    <!-- Video Background -->
    <video 
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      playsinline
      preload="auto"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    >
      <source src="/videos/system-integration-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
    
    <!-- Dark Overlay for Text Readability -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/45 z-[1]"></div>

    <!-- Hero Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-[48px] md:text-[36px] sm:text-[24px] text-white mb-4 leading-[1.2] font-normal tracking-[-0.5px]">
        System Integration
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-base sm:text-sm text-[#f0f0f0] leading-relaxed font-normal max-w-[600px] mx-auto">
        Connect CRMs, accounting, operations, and data systems. One connected stack.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-6 sm:px-6">
    <!-- SECTION 1: The Problem -->
    <section class="pt-24 md:pt-16 sm:pt-12 pb-12">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-6 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Your Systems Should Work Together
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.8] font-normal">
          Most businesses operate with 8-12 disconnected tools. Each solves a problem. None talk to each other. The result: data silos, manual data entry, teams spending 10+ hours a week moving information between systems, and leadership making decisions on incomplete information.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.8] font-normal">
          System integration connects your tools automatically. Not with complex middleware. With clean, purpose-built connections that make your existing technology work exponentially better.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 2: Integration Patterns -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-12 md:mb-8 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What We Connect
      </h2>
      
      <ul class="grid md:grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-1 gap-12 md:gap-8 sm:gap-8 list-none">
        <!-- Pattern 1: CRM ↔ Accounting -->
        <li class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            CRM ↔ Accounting
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Revenue Alignment Without Reconciliation
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-[1.8] font-normal">
            Deal closes in CRM → Invoice generates automatically → Status syncs back
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> Real-time revenue visibility without manual reconciliation
          </p>
        </li>

        <!-- Pattern 2: Operations ↔ Finance -->
        <li class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Operations ↔ Finance
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Margin Visibility in Real Time
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-[1.8] font-normal">
            Project costs and timelines flow automatically → Finance sees actual margin
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> Real-time profitability without spreadsheets
          </p>
        </li>

        <!-- Pattern 3: Customer Data ↔ Everywhere -->
        <li class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Customer Data ↔ Everywhere
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            One Source of Truth
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-[1.8] font-normal">
            Unified customer record → Changes propagate → No duplicates
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> Single view of customer across all systems
          </p>
        </li>

        <!-- Pattern 4: Operations ↔ Communications -->
        <li class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Operations ↔ Communications
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Context Flows Everywhere
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-[1.8] font-normal">
            Support sees project context → Sales sees delivery history → Delivery sees contracts
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> No information silos between teams
          </p>
        </li>

        <!-- Pattern 5: Legacy ↔ Modern -->
        <li class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Legacy ↔ Modern
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Old Systems Stay Productive
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-[1.8] font-normal">
            Legacy data flows to modern dashboards → No re-entry required
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> Phased modernization without rip-and-replace
          </p>
        </li>

        <!-- Pattern 6: Custom Data Flows -->
        <li class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8 md:border-b-0 sm:border-b-0">
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Custom Data Flows
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.6]">
            Purpose-Built Connections
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3 leading-[1.8] font-normal">
            Any system to any system → Custom middleware if needed → Real-time or scheduled
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Result:</span> Flexibility to connect anything
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3: How We Build It -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-12 md:mb-8 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        How We Build It
      </h2>
      
      <ol class="list-none space-y-0">
        <li class="py-8 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2 font-normal">
            Step 1
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Map Your Current State
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            We understand how your business actually operates. What tools you use, where the biggest inefficiencies are, what systems you might add. We identify the highest-impact integrations to build first.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="py-8 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2 font-normal">
            Step 2
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Design the Connected Stack
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            We design clean, purposeful integrations. Identify data flows, determine real-time vs. scheduled syncing, plan for reliability and future growth.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="py-8 border-b border-gray-200">
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2 font-normal">
            Step 3
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Build and Validate
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            We implement iteratively. Start with highest-impact connections, validate data flows, handle edge cases, ensure monitoring is in place.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="py-8 border-b-0">
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2 font-normal">
            Step 4
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Deploy and Transition
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            We hand over a complete, documented system. Training for your team, monitoring configured, clear process for adding new connections in the future.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4: What You Get -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-12 md:mb-8 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        What Changes
      </h2>
      
      <ul class="list-none space-y-0">
        <li class="py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Connected Systems</span> — Data flows automatically between tools
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Eliminated Manual Steps</span> — Hours of data entry gone
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Unified Information</span> — One source of truth
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Real-Time Visibility</span> — Dashboards always current
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Scaled Capacity</span> — Same team handles more volume
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="py-4 border-b-0">
          <p class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            <span class="font-normal">Future-Proof</span> — New tools integrate cleanly
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 5: Common Questions -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-12 md:mb-8 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Questions
      </h2>
      
      <ul class="list-none space-y-0">
        <li class="py-8 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            How long does integration take?
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Simple integrations: 2-4 weeks. Complex multi-system builds: 8-12 weeks. We scope timeline during discovery.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="py-8 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Will you disrupt our operations?
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            No. We build integrations alongside existing systems, test thoroughly, then switch them on. Zero downtime.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="py-8 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            What if we change systems later?
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Everything is documented. Integration documentation makes it easier to replicate connections in new systems. You're not locked in.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="py-8 border-b border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            Do you maintain the integrations?
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Yes. Maintenance is included in Build + Maintain or Build + Operate models. API changes, system updates—we keep things working.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li class="py-8 border-b-0">
          <p class="text-base text-black mb-2 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
            What about data security?
          </p>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal">
            Integrations move through secure channels. Only required data flows between systems. No credentials stored insecurely. Full audit logs.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 6: Who This Works For -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-12">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-12 md:mb-8 sm:mb-8 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Who This Works For
      </h2>
      
      <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
        <li class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Growing companies running multiple tools
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Professional services firms connecting operations and finance
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Sales-driven businesses understanding true customer economics
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Lean operations teams automating manual work
        </li>
        <li class="text-base text-black leading-[1.6] font-normal">
          Companies with legacy systems not wanting to rip and replace
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 7: CTA -->
    <section class="pt-12 pb-24 md:pb-16 sm:pb-12 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-[32px] md:text-[24px] sm:text-[24px] text-black mb-4 font-normal leading-[1.4]">
        Ready to integrate?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] font-normal mb-8 max-w-[600px] mx-auto">
        Let's start with understanding your current state—what tools you use, where manual effort exists, what visibility you're missing.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block px-8 py-3 bg-black text-white text-sm font-normal hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity">
        Start a conversation
      </a>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- Back Link -->
  <section class="py-8 px-6 border-t border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-[900px] mx-auto">
      <a href="/ai-integration-automation" class="text-base text-gray-600 hover:text-black transition-colors font-normal">
        ← Back to AI Integration & Automation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<style>
  /* Video background positioning */
  section video {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    min-width: 100%;
    min-height: 100%;
    width: auto;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  /* Mobile video fixes */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    section video {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
  }

  /* iOS Safari video fixes */
  @supports (-webkit-touch-callout: none) {
    section video {
      -webkit-transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    }
  }
</style>
</Layout>
